title: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
overview: Journalist Mikael Blomkvist is aided in his search for a woman who has been missing for forty years by Lisbeth Salander, a young computer hacker.

title: The Usual Suspects
overview: A sole survivor tells of the twisty events leading up to a horrific gun battle on a boat, which began when five criminals met at a seemingly random police lineup.

title: Primal Fear
overview: An altar boy is accused of murdering a priest, and the truth is buried several layers deep.

title: The Hateful Eight
overview: In the dead of a Wyoming winter, a bounty hunter and his prisoner find shelter in a cabin currently inhabited by a collection of nefarious characters.
stars: ['Samuel L. Jackson', 'Kurt Russell', 'Jennifer Jason Leigh', 'Walton Goggins']

title: In a Lonely Place
overview: A potentially violent screenwriter is a murder suspect until his lovely neighbor clears him. However, she soon starts to have her doubts.

title: Män som hatar kvinnor
overview: A journalist is aided by a young female hacker in his search for the killer of a woman who has been dead for forty years.

title: Mystic River
overview: The lives of three men who were childhood friends are shattered when one of them has a family tragedy.

title: Glengarry Glen Ross
overview: An examination of the machinations behind the scenes at a real estate office.

title: M - Eine Stadt sucht einen Mörder
overview: When the police in a German city are unable to catch a child-murderer, other criminals join in the manhunt.

title: Der Name der Rose
overview: An intellectually nonconformist friar investigates a series of mysterious deaths in an isolated abbey.

title: The 39 Steps
overview: A man in London tries to help a counter-espionage Agent. But when the Agent is killed, and the man stands accused, he must go on the run to save himself and stop a spy ring which is trying to steal top secret information.

title: Wind River
overview: A veteran hunter helps an FBI agent investigate the murder of a young woman on a Wyoming Native American reservation.

title: In the Heat of the Night
overview: A black police detective is asked to investigate a murder in a racially hostile southern town.

title: Double Indemnity
overview: An insurance representative lets himself be talked by a seductive housewife into a murder/insurance fraud scheme that arouses the suspicion of an insurance investigator.

title: The Night of the Hunter
overview: A religious fanatic marries a gullible widow whose young children are reluctant to tell him where their real daddy hid the $10,000 he'd stolen in a robbery.

title: The Killing
overview: Crook Johnny Clay assembles a five man team to plan and execute a daring race-track robbery.

title: Le samouraï
overview: After professional hitman Jef Costello is seen by witnesses his efforts to provide himself an alibi drive him further into a corner.

title: Salinui chueok
overview: In a small Korean province in 1986, two detectives struggle with the case of multiple young women being found raped and murdered by an unknown culprit.

title: Witness for the Prosecution
overview: A veteran British barrister must defend his client in a murder trial that has surprise after surprise.

title: Inside Man
overview: A police detective, a bank robber, and a high-power broker enter high-stakes negotiations after the criminal's brilliant heist spirals into a hostage situation.
